===Proper Noun===
'''pseudogout'''
{{wikipedia}}

{{etym}}: from [[pseudo]]- false and [[gout]].

#A medical condition with [[symptom]]s resembling [[gout]] but caused by [[precipitation]] of calcium pyrophosphate dihydrate crystals in the joints instead of monosodium ureate crystals. 

Also called [[calcium pyrophosphate dihydrate deposition disease]] which is abbreviated as the acronym [[CPPD]].

